==English==

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|wedʰ}}
From {{inh|en|enm|wedden}}, {{m|enm|weddien}}, from {{inh|en|ang|weddian||to pledge; wed}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wadjōną||to pledge}}, from {{m|gem-pro|*wadją}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*wedʰ-||to pledge}}. Cognate with Scots {{m|sco|wed}}, {{m|sco|wod}}, {{m|sco|wad||to wed}}, {{cog|stq|wädje||to bet, wager}}, {{cog|fy|wedzje||to bet, wager}}, Low German and Dutch {{m|nl|wedden||to bet}}, German {{m|de|wetten||to bet}}, Danish {{m|da|vædde||to bet}}, Swedish {{m|sv|vädja||to appeal}}, Icelandic {{m|is|veðja||to bet}}. Related also to {{l|en|gage}}, {{l|en|engage}}, and {{l|en|wage}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|wĕdʹ}}, {{IPA|/ˈwɛd/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-wed.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
